section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidiareportedfiscal third-quarter earningsand revenue that topped Wall Street expectations on Wednesday and provided stronger-than-expected sales guidance for the fourth quarter.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Shares of the AI chipmaker rose more than 4% in extended trading.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Here's how the company did, compared with estimates from analysts polled by LSEG:
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia said it expects about $65 billion in sales in the current quarter, versus $61.66 billion expected by analysts.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: The company said net income in the quarter rose 65% to $31.91 billion, or $1.30 per share, from $19.31 billion, or 78 cents per share, in the year-ago period.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia has become the most valuable publicly traded company, mostly on insatiable demand for its AI chips, called GPUs. Nvidia countsMicrosoft,Amazon,Google,Oracle, andMetaas customers. Its chips are used by all the leading tech companies to develop new artificial intelligence models.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia's sales and outlook are closely watched by the technology industry as a sign for the health of the AI boom.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: "There's been a lot of talk about an AI bubble," Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang told investors on an earnings call. "From our vantage point, we see something very different."
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia's most important business is data center sales. Nvidia said it had $51.2 billion in data center sales, easily surpassing analyst expectations for $49.09 billion in sales during the quarter, a 66% rise on a year-over-year basis.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Of that, $43 billion in revenue was for "compute," or the company's GPUs. The company said that much of the growth was driven by initial sales of the company's GB300 chips. Networking, or parts that allow scores of GPUs to work as one computer, accounted for $8.2 billion in data center sales.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia finance chief Colette Kress said in a statement that the company's best-selling chip family is now Blackwell Ultra, the second-generation version of the company's Blackwell chips.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia's report comes a few weeks after the company's megacap peers, and leading customers, issued their quarterly results. Microsoft, Meta, Amazon and Alphabet all lifted their forecasts for capital expenditures due to their AI buildouts, and now collectively expect tospendmore than $380 billion this year.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Huang said in a statement that "cloud GPUs are sold out," addressing investor concerns over the company's rapidly growing sales going to a handful of cloud providers called hyperscalers which need to find end-users for the chips.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Huangin October saidthat the company has $500 billion in orders, for 2025 and 2026 combined, for its AI chips.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: "The number will grow," Kress said on an earnings call with analysts.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Before the AI boom, Nvidia was best-known for making chips for playing 3D video games. Nvidia said it had $4.3 billion in gaming revenue, up 30% from the year-ago period.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Another legacy line item for Nvidia is its professional visualization business, which reported $760 million in sales during the quarter, up 56% on a year-over-year basis. That included sales from a product called DGX Spark, which is Nvidia's AI desktop computer that was announced earlier this year.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: The company has also highlighted robotics as one of its most important growth areas. Third-quarter automotive and robotics sales totaled $592 million, up 32% on an annual basis.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia said that it was "disappointed" that it cannot ship current-generation Blackwell chips to China. Although the company got export licenses for the H20 chip, Kress said that it only had $50 million of sales during the quarter.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: "Sizable purchase orders never materialized in the quarter due to geopolitical issues and the increasingly competitive market in China," Kress said.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

chunk_text: Nvidia said it made $12.5 billion of share repurchases and paid $243 million in dividends during the quarter.
section_title: Nvidia shares rise on stronger-than-expected revenue, forecast

document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: Nvidia (NVDA) reported its third quarter earnings on Wednesday, beating analysts' estimates on the top and bottom lines and offering a better-than-anticipated outlook.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: For the fourth quarter, Nvidia projects revenue of $65 billion plus or minus 2%. Wall Street was expecting revenue of $62 billion.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: “Blackwell sales are off the charts, and cloud GPUs are sold out,” CEO Jensen Huang said in a statement.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: “We’ve entered the virtuous cycle of AI. The AI ecosystem is scaling fast — with more new foundation model makers, more AI startups, across more industries, and in more countries. AI is going everywhere, doing everything, all at once," he added.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: Nvidia stock rose more than 5% on the news. The chipmaker's report buoyed other AI companies, with AMD's stock rising nearly 4% and Micron (MU) climbing more than 3% in after-hours action. Amazon (AMZN), Google (GOOG), Meta (META), and Microsoft (MSFT) stock also rose slightly.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: For Q3, Nvidia saw earnings per share (EPS) of $1.30 on revenue of $57.01 billion. Analysts were anticipating EPS of $1.26 on revenue of $55.2 billion, according to Bloomberg consensus data. The company saw EPS and revenue of $0.81 and $35.1 billion, respectively, in the same period last year.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: The AI giant's data center business brought in $51.2 billion versus estimates of $49.3 billion. Nvidia's gaming revenue was $4.3 billion, just short of the $4.4 billion estimate.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: "Blackwell Ultra is now our leading architecture across all customer categories while our prior Blackwell architecture saw continued strong demand," CFO Colette Kress said in a statement.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: Revenue from its China-specific H20 chip was "insignificant," she added.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: Nvidia's report comes after the company's market capitalization briefly eclipsed $5 trillion last month.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: Ahead of the earnings announcement, Peter Thiel's hedge fund sold off its entire roughly $100 million stake in Nvidia. SoftBank Group (SFTBY) also unloaded all of its Nvidia stock, valued at $5.8 billion, as the company seeks to fund its own enormous AI bets.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: It also follows remarks from rival Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) CEO Lisa Su during the company's Financial Analyst Day, during which she said that she believes the data center market will be worthas much as $1 trillion by 2030.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: Nvidia stockis up more than 37% year to date and 25% over the last 12 months. Shares of AMD are up 82% year-to-date and 58% over the last 12 months.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: Despite those gains, the AI trade gained a major detractor last week in investor Michael Burry, who famously shorted the housing market ahead of the 2008 financial crisis.In a post on X, Burry claimed that companies, including Meta (META) and Oracle (ORCL), are artificially boosting their earnings results by understating the depreciation of data center equipment.
section_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'
document_title: Nvidia stock soars after Q3 earnings, forecasts top estimates with sales for AI chips 'off the charts'

chunk_text: During Nvidia's earnings call, Kress appeared to hit back at the claim, saying Nvidia's accelerators have a long useful life thanks to the company's CUDA software and that its 6-year-old A100 GPUs are still running because of updates to CUDA over time.
